snippet.textDisplay: I remember attending weddings with such a feel. In “androon”(interior) city mohalla of extended family when I was a kid. Those were the best. As kids we would have cotton candy, handmade “dug dugees” which were these small cars with colorful callophane paper that would hit the back and make a sound when you riled them with a string. Then slowly the families moved out of interior cities and even those who remained preferred to have weddings in big formal halls. Completely took away the charm of weddings which my kids will never know
